2443:+summaryLines.push(`An exhaustive pairwise screen of standardized two-feature products found a concentrated interaction pattern. After adjustment for all 77 main effects, the largest valid interactions involved feature_046 with feature_031 (${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_031", "feature_046").beta, 5)} months per SD-product), feature_069 (+${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_069", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_062 (${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_062", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_063 (${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_063", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), and feature_010 (+${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_010", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), all p<1e-300.`);
2444:+summaryLines.push(`A joint model containing all main effects plus the top 20 interaction candidates preserved the same feature_046-centered heterogeneity: feature_031 by feature_046 (${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_031", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_069 by feature_046 (+${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_069", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_062 by feature_046 (${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_062", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_063 by feature_046 (${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_063", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), and feature_010 by feature_046 (+${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_010", "feature_046").beta, 5)}) remained independently significant.`);
2446:+summaryLines.push(`For continuous feature_062, the unadjusted slope was ${round(slope062By046[0].slopePerSd, 5)} months/SD when feature_046=0 and ${round(slope062By046[1].slopePerSd, 5)} months/SD when feature_046=1, matching the negative feature_062 by feature_046 interaction. For feature_044, the positive slope was weaker when feature_039=1 (${round(slope044By039[1].slopePerSd, 5)} months/SD) than when feature_039=0 (+${round(slope044By039[0].slopePerSd, 5)} months/SD).`);
2449:+summaryLines.push(`Quadratic probes suggested that the linear feature_044 effect had a statistically detectable but small concave component (${round(quadraticResults.find((item) => item.name === "feature_044").betaQuadratic, 5)} months for standardized z^2, p=${formatP(quadraticResults.find((item) => item.name === "feature_044").pQuadratic)}). The feature_062 quadratic term was ${round(quadraticResults.find((item) => item.name === "feature_062").betaQuadratic, 5)} months (p=${formatP(quadraticResults.find((item) => item.name === "feature_062").pQuadratic)}), much smaller than its linear and interaction terms.`);
2452:+summaryLines.push(`The cohort shows a strong multivariable signal for pfs_months. Main effects explain substantial variation (R^2=${round(1 - allMainModel.rss / yCenteredSS, 6)}), and adding the leading interaction candidates increases R^2 to ${round(jointInteractions.r2, 6)}. The most clinically interpretable pattern is not a single marker alone but heterogeneity around feature_046: its favorable association with pfs_months is reduced in feature_031=1 and feature_063=1 contexts, increased in feature_069=1 and feature_010=1 contexts, and coupled with a stronger adverse feature_062 slope.`);
