5934:+summaryLines.push(`An exhaustive pairwise screen of standardized two-feature products found a concentrated interaction pattern. After adjustment for all 77 main effects, the largest valid interactions involved feature_046 with feature_031 (${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_031", "feature_046").beta, 5)} months per SD-product), feature_069 (+${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_069", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_062 (${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_062", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_063 (${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_063", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), and feature_010 (+${round(adjustedInteractionResult("feature_010", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), all p<1e-300.`);
5935:+summaryLines.push(`A joint model containing all main effects plus the top 20 interaction candidates preserved the same feature_046-centered heterogeneity: feature_031 by feature_046 (${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_031", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_069 by feature_046 (+${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_069", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_062 by feature_046 (${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_062", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), feature_063 by feature_046 (${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_063", "feature_046").beta, 5)}), and feature_010 by feature_046 (+${round(jointInteractionResult("feature_010", "feature_046").beta, 5)}) remained independently significant.`);
5937:+summaryLines.push(`For continuous feature_062, the unadjusted slope was ${round(slope062By046[0].slopePerSd, 5)} months/SD when feature_046=0 and ${round(slope062By046[1].slopePerSd, 5)} months/SD when feature_046=1, matching the negative feature_062 by feature_046 interaction. For feature_044, the positive slope was weaker when feature_039=1 (${round(slope044By039[1].slopePerSd, 5)} months/SD) than when feature_039=0 (+${round(slope044By039[0].slopePerSd, 5)} months/SD).`);
